NeuroCore Simulation-3 Master Execution Guide

Version: Production Readiness Simulation
Scenario Duration: 2 Months
Purpose: Validate NeuroCore as a production-grade autonomous operating platform using a realistic emergency nutrition programme executed entirely through the UI and APIs.

Simulation Objective

Run an end-to-end two-month emergency nutrition programme without manual database edits.

Exercise CRM, project management, AI employees, workflows, Brevo email, Google Workspace, approvals, memory, reporting and audit logs.

Record evidence for every action and classify failures as Critical, High, Medium or Low.

Do not modify source code during execution. Remediation is a separate phase.

Programme Scenario

Customer: Ministry of Health.

Programme: Two-Month Flood Emergency Nutrition Response.

Budget: USD 850,000.

Coverage: 4 districts, 40,000 households, 18,000 children under five, 6,000 pregnant/lactating women.

Partners: UNICEF, WFP, WHO, Provincial Health Department and two NGOs.

Outputs: Rapid assessment, screening, referral, treatment support, monitoring and final report.

