Execution Rules

Everything must be created through the application as a real customer would.

Every generated entity must be linked correctly (customer, project, stages, tasks, approvals, communications, emails, meetings).

Every AI answer must be grounded in stored project knowledge.

Capture screenshots, API responses and audit IDs where available.

Retry transient failures up to three times before marking FAILED.

Detailed Simulation Phases

Week 1: Create lead, qualify opportunity, schedule meetings, send proposal via Brevo, create customer, create project, sync meetings with Google Workspace.

Week 2: Discovery interview, collect objectives, KPIs, beneficiaries, risks, donors, reporting requirements, produce >95% completeness.

Week 3: Auto-create departments, AI employees, workspaces, knowledge base, dashboards, approvals and communication channels.

Week 4: Generate WBS, logframe, implementation plan, Gantt, procurement plan, risk register, budget and monitoring framework.

Week 5: Generate 200+ tasks with dependencies, priorities, owners and approval chains. Validate no duplicates or orphan records.

Week 6: Run collaboration: procurement requests, finance approvals, HR recruitment, logistics updates, donor communications, executive decisions.

Week 7: Inject failures: AI timeout, Redis restart, worker restart, Brevo error, Google Calendar outage, malformed LLM output. Verify retries and recovery.

Week 8: Produce reports, dashboards, lessons learned, close project, archive knowledge, generate executive audit.

